text: Prunus tetradenia is a species of Prunus native to the montane cloud forests of Mexico.Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 52: 309 (1915) It is a tree 6 to 20m tall. The resplendent quetzal consumes its fruit. ==References== tetradenia Category:Endemic flora of Mexico Category:Trees of Mexico Category:Plants described in 1915
